Although this is your standard run of the mill NTR, there is something that can be taken away from reading this. And it's actually fairly wholesome.
On Page 17, Yuu-Kun says "Just talking to her about my feelings made me feel better. Even now, both my mind and my body are refreshed" As someone who has actually done this before, I can confirm that this is entirely true. I once liked a girl, a childhood friend one could say. I already confessed to her once before in elementary school, but it was pretty half-assed. I'll spare you the details, but I was a dumb kid. In 8th grade, I confessed in a slightly more reasonable manner, over an Email.

A cheap cop-out on my part, but it was the most effective way for me to convey my feelings for her without screwing up. I told her how I truly felt about her but I didn't ask her out because I was perfectly fine remaining her friend. And let me tell you, I felt so, so much better having told her how I felt about her. Just the simple knowledge that she knew my feelings, it quite literally felt like a weight was lifted off my shoulders. Forgive me for the story my point is; kings and queens if there is someone out there that you fancy, do yourself a favor and tell them how you feel. I know it's a directive easier said than done, but believe me, you'll feel a lot better knowing you took the chance rather than wallow in your bed at night wondering what could've been. TL;DR If there is someone you like, confess them. In the end, you'll be a lot better off knowing you took action rather than in-action.
